Pages = {1027-1035},
Abstract = {Plants of the family Iridaceae are well represented in the grassland
   vegetation of southern Brazil, occurring in the Pampa and Atlantic
   Forest biomes. Nevertheless, little is known about the taxonomy and
   evolution of Iridaceae species in southern Brazil. The main goal of this
   review is to compile published information about South American
   Iridaceae, and to discuss the evolution and genetic diversity of the
   family presenting our own research data in the light of the published
   literature. The main focus is on the genera Calydorea, Cypella,
   Herbertia, and Sisyrinchium. Aspects of reproductive system and of
   pollinator attraction are also discussed.},
