Year = {1991},
Volume = {40},
Number = {3},
Pages = {199-207},
Abstract = {The structural organization of the stigma-ovary tract, of the ovule, and
   of the embryo sac was studied by optical and electron microscopy in buds
   and flowers of saffron (Crocus sativus L.) at different stages of
   development.  The saffron stigma is of the dry type and the papillae are
   covered by a continuous cuticle.  The ovary has septa enlarged in its
   upper part and three internal canals covered with septal nectaries.  The
   relation between these particular structures and the existence of
   possible growth substances in these parts of the pistil is pointed out.},
